args: Alas, I desired something I can never have.
Yet even armed with that knowledge,\nwhy do I continue to...?
I'm sorry, Mym, but I cannot accept.
Your present is ME! Don't you want me?!\nCome baaack!
(Still the lives of human and dragon must\nbe two very singular things.)
(They cannot hope to share a lifetime\ntogether, so why would she...?)
Oof. You feeling okay, Nefaria?\nIt almost looks as though the undead\nwalk among us!
I'm sorry—that was in poor taste.
If you are amiable to it, might I speak\nwith you about a matter?
What is it? I'm happy to listen.
Your counsel will be much appreciated.
You see, I know now what it is that I\ndesired in my former life.
Or...not? I'm going to guess not.
So what was it that you wanted?
Wait, but that doesn't make sense.\nI thought you told me you didn't\nhave a special someone in your life?
It was not love that I desired, per se.
I merely grew tired of carrying the mantle\nof leadership on my own.
I wanted someone at my side to share in\nthe burdens and pressures of my life.
I wanted to live alongside that person;\nto travel through life with them.
It is something I have long desired,\nand yet something I can never have.
For I am a singular being—an immortal\nin all but name. None exist who could\nshare my life.
I think I understand your pain.
My darling and I... Well, we cannot go\nthrough life in the same way, either.
The truth of that is very painful.
I thought you might suffer as I do in this.
However, given such pain, why do you\ncontinue to persist in your affections for\n{player_name}?
Why do I continue to...? Heh.\nAAAAAH HA HA HA HA!
I meant the question most soberly.
You CLEARLY have never been in love.

Well then, let me explain something.
When you're in love, you can try to ignore
it or avoid it or bury it deep, but it doesn't
matter. It's ALWAYS going to come out.
Oh, it is. Why, at any moment, you might\nfind the face of your beloved floating\nthrough your mind!
And the merest thought of them fills your\nheart up to bursting!
Sometimes you even act without knowing\nwhat you're doing—or why. It's like your\nbody is no longer your own.
Are you saying your body acts of its own\nvolition, without the input of the mind?
Pretty much. That's how it is for me,\nat any rate.
I don't know the future—which is often\nTERRIBLY vexing—but I do know that\nI can't do anything about these feelings.
Ah. So for you, it is the present that is\nmost important, not the future.
Eeeee! All this talking about my love for\nmy darling makes me want to see him!
I'm off, Nefaria. Oh, and try not to worry\ntoo much about this, all right?
Thank you, Mym. I feel rather unbound\nfrom my recent burdens.
None can know the future, but I CAN learn\nto understand my feelings in the now.
Such as the peace I felt at the side of\n{player_name}...
Whew! That Mym is a force of nature.
No matter how many times she told me to,\nI can't accept her as a gift. It's just...weird.
Hey, Nefaria. It looks like you're feeling\na little better.
I was worried when you took off for the\ncastle the other day.
My apologies if I caused consternation.\nI am well now.
In fact, if it is not too much to ask...
Might you return with me to that location?
Sure. I'm free right now, actually.
...Ah, but I feel my heart ease when I\nam in this place.
It's almost like I want to stay here forever.
Indeed, I feel the same way.\nBut that is an impossible dream.
...Or mayhap my wish is already in the\nprocess of being granted.
The ease which I feel here will surely\nremain etched upon my mind.
It will never fade—it is eternal.
I know I'm going to remember the times\nwe've shared here.
Strange. I always thought the flow of time\nto be a great wave none could stand\nagainst, but now I see I was mistaken.
The past, present, and future all exist in\nthe depths of my heart.
A moment is forever—and it is within that\nmoment where we live.
